---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Thomas Brady" description="Path, instruments, marks, and lineage.">
  <section class="about">
    <!-- 01 — PATH -->
    <div class="section-divider reveal">
      <span class="section-number">01 — Path</span>
      <hr />
    </div>

    <!-- Pando Industries -->
    <div class="exp-card reveal">
      <div class="exp-card__header">
        <div>
          <h3 class="exp-card__role">Founder</h3>
          <div class="exp-card__org">Pando Industries</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card__date">2022–Present</div>
      </div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Built <strong>Notice</strong>, an iOS app for interoceptive awareness training, in 3 days using Claude Code — designed two-tier AI architecture integrating Apple's on-device Foundation Models for real-time context capture with Claude API for longitudinal pattern analysis; first iOS app, learned Swift/SwiftUI through AI-accelerated development</li>
        <li>Developed <strong>Scholion</strong>, an interactive argument visualization tool mapping epistemic dependencies in scientific reasoning — grounded in Toulmin argumentation theory, Doyle's truth-maintenance systems, and Lakatos's research programme methodology; built working prototype and published thesis at thbrdy.dev</li>
        <li>Authored 10,000-word research framework on coordination infrastructure under AI acceleration, synthesizing formal results on superlinear coordination costs with Weick's sensemaking theory and Scott's legibility framework to articulate a novel "legibility inversion" thesis</li>
        <li>Won 1st place at AI in Motion Lab Automation Hackathon (50 builders, 24 hours) — built "Close the Loop," a multi-agent system with live integration between Opentrons liquid handler and Cephla microscope, using LLM orchestration to generate protocols from meeting discussions and close feedback loops with imaging data</li>
        <li>Assembled team and attracted investor interest for biopharma venture building multi-agent systems for automated lab protocols on robotic platforms</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="exp-card__tags">
        <span>Claude Code</span><span>Multi-Agent Systems</span><span>SwiftUI</span><span>Research</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- H2O.ai -->
    <div class="exp-card reveal">
      <div class="exp-card__header">
        <div>
          <h3 class="exp-card__role">Senior Director, Product Management</h3>
          <div class="exp-card__org">H2O.ai</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card__date">2021–2022</div>
      </div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Led product strategy for H2O.ai's core portfolio representing <strong>85% of revenue</strong>, driving 40% customer base growth and $400K increase in average deal size</li>
        <li>Co-developed H2O Feature Store with AT&T through daily hands-on technical collaboration — led the co-development effort, built all demo notebooks and example use cases, validated prototypes through iterative customer feedback; attracted <strong>$50M+ pipeline</strong> including Workday, PayPal, and Bank of America</li>
        <li>Transformed Driverless AI into cloud-native service, reducing deployment time 10x; developed hybrid deployment strategy meeting enterprise security requirements while expanding into pharmaceuticals, supply chain, and business planning verticals</li>
        <li>Ran AutoML experiments alongside CTO Arno Candel, testing features directly with customers and presenting strategic vision to Gartner and Forrester analysts</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="exp-card__tags">
        <span>AutoML</span><span>Feature Store</span><span>Cloud-Native</span><span>Enterprise ML</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- AWS -->
    <div class="exp-card reveal">
      <div class="exp-card__header">
        <div>
          <h3 class="exp-card__role">Amazon Web Services — Product Management</h3>
          <div class="exp-card__org">AWS</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card__date">2018–2021</div>
      </div>

      <div class="exp-card__subrole">Product Lead, HPC & Elastic Fabric Adapter (2021)</div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Authored HPC/EFA strategy positioning AWS against Azure/Oracle in <strong>$10B market</strong>; launched multi-slot instances and RDMA GPU enabling 100K+ core clusters</li>
        <li>Designed Hpc6a pricing/ring-fencing strategy balancing $2B addressable market vs cannibalization risk; drove wins with Rescale ($45M), Siemens ($112M), Rivian, Maxar, and Boom Aerospace</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="exp-card__subrole">Product Lead, AI & Machine Learning Research (2020–2021)</div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Worked directly with researchers across graph ML, causality, LLMs, and deep learning compilers to identify which research capabilities had product potential; authored research-to-product strategy for <strong>$20M org (200 people)</strong></li>
        <li>Shaped AWS's first LLM (M5/M*) with Alex Smola, George Karypis, and Trishul Chilimbi — worked in notebooks alongside research teams, defined use cases for Ads/Alexa/Search that grounded the research in commercial applications</li>
        <li>Built evaluation framework that <strong>doubled research commercialization rate</strong> — assessed real-world applicability, technical readiness, and market potential through structured notional press releases, working prototypes, and customer validation</li>
        <li>Launched <strong>Neptune ML</strong> from research concept to production service, now powering RAG applications; drove distributed training framework delivering 4x performance improvement at 7x cost reduction</li>
        <li>Created multi-dimensional model deployment system enabling instant global deployment for Amazon's catalog and ads teams, reducing operational costs by 100x</li>
        <li>Drove turnaround of AWS deep learning toolchain (now <strong>Neuron SDK</strong>) through unified approach, reducing inference latency and operational costs by 60%</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="exp-card__subrole">Product Manager, Solutions Architecture (2018–2020)</div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Scaled technical workshop program from pilot to <strong>40K+ events</strong> generating $3.4B pipeline; wrote Python/SQL to automate reporting and track conversion metrics</li>
        <li>Built automated resource provisioning platform enabling 4K+ solutions architects to deliver workshops across 175+ AWS services; maintained 4.4/5.0 satisfaction</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="exp-card__tags">
        <span>Neptune ML</span><span>Neuron SDK</span><span>HPC</span><span>LLMs</span><span>Graph ML</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Senate Armed Services -->
    <div class="exp-card reveal">
      <div class="exp-card__header">
        <div>
          <h3 class="exp-card__role">Defense Policy Advisor</h3>
          <div class="exp-card__org">United States Senate Armed Services Committee</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card__date">2015–2017</div>
      </div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Architected transformation of Army's <strong>$3B intelligence enterprise</strong> (DCGS-A) — evaluated competing technical approaches, developed new requirements and procurement strategy that cut yearly dev/ops costs by 65%</li>
        <li>Created investment framework for evaluating emerging defense technologies (IT systems, advanced materials, autonomous systems), guiding multi-billion dollar Congressional investment decisions</li>
        <li>Drove adoption of 30+ legislative initiatives spanning military IT modernization and commercial technology integration; led Stryker vehicle modernization initiative, increasing investment 4x and accelerating delivery by 18 months</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="exp-card__tags">
        <span>Defense Policy</span><span>Procurement</span><span>Legislative Strategy</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- UW Emergency Management -->
    <div class="exp-card reveal">
      <div class="exp-card__header">
        <div>
          <h3 class="exp-card__role">Program Manager</h3>
          <div class="exp-card__org">University of Washington Emergency Management</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card__date">2013–2014</div>
      </div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Developed first comprehensive seismic resiliency policy for UW campus; built cross-functional working groups spanning 12 university units and multiple municipal/county agencies</li>
        <li>Secured three years of seed funding through data-driven risk assessment; authored seismic resiliency report accepted by UW Board of Regents</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="exp-card__tags">
        <span>Emergency Management</span><span>Seismic Resiliency</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Special Forces -->
    <div class="exp-card reveal">
      <div class="exp-card__header">
        <div>
          <h3 class="exp-card__role">United States Army Special Forces</h3>
          <div class="exp-card__org">U.S. Army</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card__date">2004–2012</div>
      </div>

      <div class="exp-card__subrole">Senior Manager, Operations & Intelligence (2010–2012)</div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Orchestrated operational support across six Special Forces teams executing diverse missions throughout Asia, leading 12-person team managing logistics, comms, and resource allocation with <strong>$3M budget</strong></li>
        <li>Coordinated complex plans across teams in multiple countries, optimizing resource allocation based on varying local conditions; built scalable systems for sharing operational intelligence despite varying infrastructure and security constraints</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="exp-card__subrole">Communications Program Manager (2007–2010)</div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Engineered 2,500-mile HF radio transmission from Nepal to Japan using computer modeling to simulate atmospheric conditions and design custom antenna configuration, exceeding equipment specifications by 5x</li>
        <li>Built integrated communications architecture combining vehicle-mounted radios, satellite systems, and encryption for 60+ missions in austere environments</li>
        <li>Stood up broadband satellite communications centers supporting five multinational deployments; managed $2M+ portfolio of advanced comms equipment with zero losses</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="exp-card__subrole">Special Forces Candidate / Infantryman (2004–2007)</div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Selected from top 5% of candidates (400+) for Special Forces Qualification Course; completed two-year pipeline combining advanced combat training, communications specialization, and Mandarin Chinese fluency</li>
        <li>Completed 52-week intensive Mandarin immersion program; technical training in satellite communications, radio theory, cryptography, and field operations</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="exp-card__tags">
        <span>Special Forces</span><span>Operations</span><span>Communications</span><span>Mandarin</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- DIA -->
    <div class="exp-card reveal">
      <div class="exp-card__header">
        <div>
          <h3 class="exp-card__role">Intelligence Analyst</h3>
          <div class="exp-card__org">Defense Intelligence Agency</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card__date">2004</div>
      </div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Authored strategic assessments of Chinese military leadership — backgrounds, decision-making patterns, and strategic priorities — used by senior defense and policy leaders</li>
        <li>Analyzed emerging trends in Chinese military strategy and doctrine to inform U.S. defense planning and modernization decisions</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="exp-card__tags">
        <span>Intelligence Analysis</span><span>China</span><span>Strategic Assessment</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Senate Foreign Relations -->
    <div class="exp-card reveal">
      <div class="exp-card__header">
        <div>
          <h3 class="exp-card__role">United States Senate Foreign Relations Committee</h3>
          <div class="exp-card__org">U.S. Senate</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card__date">1998–2004</div>
      </div>

      <div class="exp-card__subrole">Manager, Foreign Policy (2001–2004)</div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Spearheaded development and passage of Sudan Peace Act, managing complex stakeholder relationships across State Department, Commerce, and USAID</li>
        <li>Served as lead Asia-Pacific policy expert providing strategic analysis on international economics, counter-terrorism, and foreign assistance programs</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="exp-card__subrole">Research Analyst (1998–2001)</div>
      <ul class="exp-card__details">
        <li>Led research on critical foreign policy issues including technology export controls and international broadcasting; coordinated Congressional hearings and senior staff briefings</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="exp-card__tags">
        <span>Foreign Policy</span><span>Asia-Pacific</span><span>Legislation</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 02 — INSTRUMENTS -->
    <div class="section-divider reveal">
      <span class="section-number">02 — Instruments</span>
      <hr />
    </div>

    <div class="skills-grid reveal">
      <div class="skill-group">
        <h3>Languages & Data</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Python</li>
          <li>SQL</li>
          <li>Data Visualization</li>
          <li>A/B Testing</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="skill-group">
        <h3>AI / ML Systems</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Claude Code</li>
          <li>LLM Orchestration</li>
          <li>Multi-Agent Systems</li>
          <li>AutoML Systems</li>
          <li>Graph Algorithms</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="skill-group">
        <h3>Infrastructure</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>AWS SageMaker</li>
